
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a specific location in the node graph. It targets the [where] node under [data.read] and appends nodes retrieved from the [arguments] node using [get-nodes]. The [get-nodes] slot fetches all nodes under [.arguments], and [add] inserts these nodes into the specified path, effectively merging the argument nodes into the [where] clause of a data read operation. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to a specified location in the node graph.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves all nodes under the [.arguments] node.
 */
add:x:./*/data.read/*/where/*/and
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
